definition.value: Alteration or impairment in the processing or interpretation of sensory information can lead to abnormal perceptions or experiences.
The examiner identified the inability to name, move, or touch specific fingers.
Tactile agnosia refers to the inability to recognize objects by touch, while the inability to discriminate shape and size by touch is also a related condition.
Inability to recognize faces of familiar persons.

An intermittent cessation of airflow at the mouth and nose during sleep is known as sleep apnea. Apneas that last at least 10 seconds are considered significant, but individuals with sleep apnea may experience apneas lasting from 20 seconds up to 2 or 3 minutes. Patients may have up to 15 events per hour of sleep.
